      <h2>The Romance Linguistics Seminar</h2>
      
      <p>The Research Centre organises a regular seminar, with presentations by guest speakers from UK and international institutions, and by the Centre's own members, both staff and research students.  The seminar programme is published on this page at the start of each term.</p> 
      
      <p>Each seminar is followed by informal discussion over a glass of wine.<br><b>All are warmly invited to attend</b>.</p>
      
<h2>Trinity 2015</h2>
        <p>Seminars will be held at 5pm in room 3 of the Taylor Institution. Convenor: Prof. Martin Maiden.</p>
        <p>14 May.  Dr Alex Nicolae, University of Bucharest.<br>
        'On the structure of the Romanian Clause'</p>
            

<p>21 May. Dr Susana Afonso, University of Exeter.<br>
'Portuguese in East Timor: a variety in formation'</p>

<h2>Hilary 2015</h2>
        <p>Seminars will be held at 5pm (unless otherwise stated) in room 3 of the Taylor Institution. Convenor: Prof. Martin Maiden.</p>
        
<p>5 February. Dr Paul O'Neill, University of Sheffield<br>
'Diachronic contributions to synchronic theories of morphology: evidence from Romance verb morphology'</p>

<p>19 February. Dr Louise Esher, St John's College, Oxford.<br>
'Romance perspectives on morphome ecology and evolution' </p>

<p>5 March <b>at 5:30pm</b>. Dr Cecilia Poletto, University of Frankfurt.<br>
'Non and its companions: on the big NegP hypothesis'.</p>

<p>12 March. Dr Iris Bachmann, University of Manchester.<br>
'Changing conceptions of Portuguese (and other languages) in the digital age'</p>      
      
      <h2>Michaelmas 2014</h2>
        <p>Seminars will be held at 5pm (unless otherwise stated) in room 3 of the Taylor Institution. Convenor: Prof. Martin Maiden.</p>
        
<p>23 October at <b>5:30pm</b>. Dr Pavel Štichauer, Charles University, Prague.<br>
'VN compounds in Italian from the sixteenth century onwards: an exploitation of a word-formation pattern'</p>

<p>6 November. Dr Antonio Fortin, University of Manchester.<br>
'The expressive dimension of Spanish evaluative affixes' </p>

<p>20 November. Dr Márcia Cristina do Carmo, University College London.<br>
'Phonological variation in São Paulo Brazilian Portuguese'.</p>

<p>4 December. Dr Sandra Paoli, Balliol College, Oxford.<br>
'Between <i>friulano</i> and <i>veneto</i>: the case of <i>tergestino</i>'</p>

      
      



      
